# Git & PR workflow (MuscleCraft)

Remote: `git@github-steveloids27:SteveLoids27/MuscleCraft.git`  
Use the `github-steveloids27` SSH host so pushes authenticate as **SteveLoids27** (not steveloidsCV).

## Default branch for new work

**`dev-Steve`** — all new features and milestones are built here.

## When the user asks to build a new feature

1. **Branch** — `git checkout dev-Steve` and `git pull origin dev-Steve` (rebase if needed).
2. **Implement** — follow app-builder pipeline (plan → build → safe-code-improver → app-tester).
3. **Test** — `python3 -m pytest -v` must pass before commit.
4. **Commit** — only when the user asks to commit; never commit `.env` or secrets.
5. **Push** — `git push -u origin dev-Steve` (use `github-steveloids27` remote URL).
6. **PR** — open a pull request **into `main`** when the user asks (or when feature is complete):
   ```bash
   gh pr create --base main --head dev-Steve \
     --title "<short feature title>" \
     --body "## Summary\n- ...\n\n## Test plan\n- [ ] pytest passes\n- [ ] manual smoke test"
   ```
7. **Report** — return the PR URL to the user.

## Do not

- Push feature work directly to `main` unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Force-push `main`.
- Amend commits that were already pushed unless the user explicitly asks.

## After a PR is merged

Sync `dev-Steve` with `main` before the next feature:

```bash
git checkout dev-Steve
git pull origin main --rebase
git push origin dev-Steve
```
